.References","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/6a767a66a13c588cce3829bf1de00a1830883843/src/Lean/Server/References.lean#L211-L221","name":"Lean.Server.findModuleRefs","docLink":"./Lean/Server/References.html#Lean.Server.findModuleRefs","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/6a767a66a13c588cce3829bf1de00a1830883843/src/Lean/Server/References.lean#L199-L209","name":"Lean.Server.dedupReferences","docLink":"./Lean/Server/References.html#Lean.Server.dedupReferences","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/6a767a66a13c588cce3829bf1de00a1830883843/src/Lean/Server/References.lean#L195-L197","name":"Lean.Server.combineFvars.applyIdMap","docLink":"./Lean/Server/References.html#Lean.Server.combineFvars.applyIdMap","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/6a767a66a13c588cce3829bf1de00a1830883843/src/Lean/Server/References.lean#L190-L193","name":"Lean.Server.combineFvars.findCanonicalBinder","docLink":"./Lean/Server/References.html#Lean.Server.combineFvars.findCanonicalBinder","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/6a767a66a13c588cce3829bf1de00a1830883843/src/Lean/Server/References.lean#L160-L197","name":"Lean.Server.combineFvars","docLink":"./Lean/Server/References.html#Lean.Server.combineFvars","doc":"The `FVarId`s of a function parameter in the function's signature and body\ndiffer. However, they have `TermInfo` nodes with `binder := true` in the exact\nsame position. Moreover, macros such as do-reassignment `x := e` may create\nchains of variable definitions where a helper definition overlaps with a use\nof a variable.\n\nThis function changes every such group to use a single `FVarId` (the head of the\nchain/DAG) and gets rid of duplicate definitions.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/6a767a66a13c588cce3829bf1de00a1830883843/src/Lean/Server/References.lean#L140-L148","name":"Lean.Server.findReferences","docLink":".